      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 md:gap-8">
        <div class="lesson-card">
          <div class="linocut-icon">
            <!-- Spec / target: stacked filled lines with crosshair -->
            <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <!-- Concentric circles, dashed outer -->
              <circle cx="40" cy="40" r="30" fill="none" stroke="#E13D0F" stroke-width="3"/>
              <circle cx="40" cy="40" r="20" fill="none" stroke="#E13D0F" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="3 3"/>
              <circle cx="40" cy="40" r="10" fill="#E13D0F"/>
              <!-- Crosshair lines -->
              <line x1="40" y1="4" x2="40" y2="14" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="40" y1="66" x2="40" y2="76" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="4" y1="40" x2="14" y2="40" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <line x1="66" y1="40" x2="76" y2="40" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              <!-- Center dot in cream -->
              <circle cx="40" cy="40" r="3" fill="#F4EFE5"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-ink mb-4 leading-tight">Spec quality is the new bottleneck.</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
            You stop being blocked on "how long will this take to build" and start being
            blocked on "exactly what do I want this to do." Clarity becomes the highest-leverage
            skill you have.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="lesson-card">
          <div class="linocut-icon">
            <!-- Key: filled bow with hatching, three teeth -->
            <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <!-- Bow (filled circle) -->
              <circle cx="22" cy="40" r="14" fill="#E13D0F"/>
              <!-- Bow inner cutout (cream) -->
              <circle cx="22" cy="40" r="5" fill="#F4EFE5"/>
              <!-- Hatching on bow -->
              <line x1="15" y1="32" x2="29" y2="46" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.4"/>
              <line x1="15" y1="48" x2="29" y2="34" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.4"/>
              <!-- Shaft -->
              <rect x="36" y="36" width="32" height="8" fill="#02101D"/>
              <!-- Teeth -->
              <rect x="50" y="44" width="5" height="8" fill="#02101D"/>
              <rect x="58" y="44" width="5" height="10" fill="#02101D"/>
              <rect x="63" y="44" width="4" height="6" fill="#02101D"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-ink mb-4 leading-tight">Authority beats access.</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
            An AI that can only advise is a better search engine. An AI with commit rights,
            assigned tickets, and QA responsibility is a collaborator. The difference is
            accountability architecture.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="lesson-card">
          <div class="linocut-icon">
            <!-- Magnifier with hatching in glass and angled handle -->
            <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <!-- Glass circle, filled orange -->
              <circle cx="32" cy="32" r="18" fill="#E13D0F"/>
              <!-- Hatching inside glass (cream) -->
              <line x1="20" y1="24" x2="44" y2="24" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              <line x1="18" y1="32" x2="46" y2="32" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              <line x1="20" y1="40" x2="44" y2="40" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              <!-- Glass rim (outline) -->
              <circle cx="32" cy="32" r="18" fill="none" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3.5"/>
              <!-- Highlight reflection -->
              <path d="M22 22 Q26 18 32 18" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              <!-- Handle (filled) -->
              <rect x="48" y="48" width="22" height="8" fill="#02101D" transform="rotate(45 48 48)"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-ink mb-4 leading-tight">Judgment concentrates.</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
            When AI handles execution, every decision that stays with you becomes more
            consequential. Brand, tone, pricing, who you're building for. These can't be
            delegated. You get to be only a decision-maker.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
